  "prompt": "Are there other movies like The Secret?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several movies, documentaries, and self-help programs that share themes similar to *The Secret*, which focuses on the law of attraction and the power of positive thinking. Here are some recommendations:\n\n### Movies and Documentaries:\n1. **What the Bleep Do We Know!?** (2004)  \n   - A blend of documentary and fictional storytelling, this film explores the connection between quantum physics, consciousness, and reality.\n\n2. **The Shift** (2009)  \n   - A companion film to *The Secret*, it delves deeper into personal transformation and living a purposeful life.\n\n3. **You Can Heal Your Life** (2007)  \n   - Based on Louise Hay's teachings, this film focuses on self-love, affirmations, and the power of the mind to heal.\n\n4. **The Opus** (2017)  \n   - A spiritual documentary that explores the journey of transformation and the possibility of achieving one\u2019s dreams.\n\n5. **Down the Rabbit Hole** (2006)  \n   - An extended version of *What the Bleep Do We Know!?*, offering deeper insights into quantum physics and consciousness.\n\n---\n\n### Self-Help Programs:\n1. **The Power of Intention** (2005) by Dr. Wayne Dyer  \n   - A program that teaches how to align with universal energy to manifest your desires.\n\n2. **The Science of Getting Rich** (2012)  \n   - Based on Wallace D. Wattles' book, this program focuses on the principles of abundance and wealth creation.\n\n3. **The Tapping Solution** (2009)  \n   - A documentary that introduces Emotional Freedom Technique (EFT) as a tool for releasing negative emotions and manifesting goals.\n\n---\n\n### Books (if you\u2019re interested in exploring more):  \n1. *Think and Grow Rich* by Napoleon Hill  \n2. *The Power of Now* by Eckhart Tolle  \n3. *Ask and It Is Given* by Esther and Jerry Hicks  \n4. *The Law of Attraction* by Esther and Jerry Hicks  \n\nThese works share the underlying message that your thoughts and intentions have the power to shape your reality. Let me know if you'd like more recommendations!",
